1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:03,100
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,350 --> 00:00:07,060
Led by Carla, we tried to 
sneak into Edolas's castle,

3
00:00:07,060 --> 00:00:11,320
but their Erza, Knightwalker, was 
waiting for us, and we were captured!

4
00:00:11,320 --> 00:00:14,900
And wait, it doesn't look like I 
appear much this episode at all!

5
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:16,620
Ever heard of the prize 
for perfect attendance?

6
00:00:16,620 --> 00:00:20,040
Somebody save us, and get us outta here!

7
00:02:05,390 --> 00:02:07,300
You bastards!

8
00:02:08,270 --> 00:02:09,750
Where is everyone?

9
00:02:09,750 --> 00:02:10,690
Everyone?

10
00:02:10,950 --> 00:02:13,190
Lucy-san, Carla, and Happy!

11
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:15,230
Lucy...

12
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:18,110
Oh, you mean that woman?

13
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:22,620
Sorry, but I ain't got any use for her.

14
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:25,580
Maybe she'll be, like, executed?

15
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:30,000
Just you try hurting a hair on her head...

16
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:32,000
'Cause I'll turn you all...

17
00:02:32,970 --> 00:02:35,280
...into smoldering ashes!

18
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,880
Extalia.

19
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:51,480
Whoa, you're scary!

20
00:02:51,480 --> 00:02:55,380
Is everyone from Earthland this violent?

21
00:02:56,220 --> 00:02:58,190
Why just Lucy-san?

22
00:02:58,470 --> 00:03:00,110
What about Carla and Happy?

23
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:02,610
The Exceeds?

24
00:03:02,610 --> 00:03:04,570
That ain't Happy's name!

25
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:09,720
The Exceeds who have completed their duty 
have been sent back to their homeland.

26
00:03:10,250 --> 00:03:14,370
They're probably getting their reward 
and having a big feast about now.

27
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,380
Completed their duty?

28
00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:23,520
Returning to Edolas is a 
violation of my orders.

29
00:03:25,930 --> 00:03:27,770
I don't believe you!

30
00:03:27,770 --> 00:03:32,310
I might not know what that duty 
is, but Carla abandoned it!

31
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:35,720
Oh, no...

32
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:38,860
She fulfilled it quite well.

33
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,860
What exactly was her duty?

34
00:03:47,230 --> 00:03:49,760
You haven't figured it out yet?

35
00:04:19,780 --> 00:04:21,220
What are you doing?

36
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:25,570
Excellent work!

37
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:27,050
Who are you?

38
00:04:27,050 --> 00:04:29,300
I am simply a journalist!

39
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:33,160
With such a ceremony, I was hoping 
perhaps to take an interview?

40
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:35,610
I have nothing to tell you. Now, go!

41
00:04:35,610 --> 00:04:38,600
This is the northern end of the plaza...

42
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:42,710
I presume there are also guards 
stationed at the southern end?

43
00:04:45,460 --> 00:04:46,090
Go!

44
00:04:47,310 --> 00:04:49,550
Pardon me for disturbing your work!

45
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:04,020
Damn...

46
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:08,650
If I barge in from the front, the 
onlookers will get wrapped up in it.

47
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:11,400
What'll I do?

48
00:05:30,060 --> 00:05:33,290
Huh? Where am I?

49
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,210
Carla, wake up!

50
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,060
He-cat?

51
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:45,550
What happened to us?

52
00:05:46,110 --> 00:05:48,950
They put us to sleep.

53
00:05:49,570 --> 00:05:50,930
Then...

54
00:05:51,490 --> 00:05:53,350
Where is this place?

55
00:05:55,950 --> 00:05:57,290
Carla?

56
00:06:06,290 --> 00:06:09,530
My "information" was a trap!

57
00:06:13,610 --> 00:06:15,030
That's not true!

58
00:06:15,030 --> 00:06:17,580
We were just found by accident!

59
00:06:17,580 --> 00:06:19,530
It wasn't your fault, Carla!

60
00:06:24,270 --> 00:06:25,440
Even though I swore...

61
00:06:26,550 --> 00:06:29,520
I swore to protect Wendy...

62
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:33,070
No matter what happens, I will protect Wendy!

63
00:06:34,640 --> 00:06:36,070
I swore...

64
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:49,540
You are the ones who have completed 
their duty on Earthland?

65
00:06:50,250 --> 00:06:51,930
Ichiya?

66
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,330
You have excellent parfum.

67
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,810
And wait, a cat?

68
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:59,350
Why are you so surprised?

69
00:06:59,350 --> 00:07:01,480
We are all Exceeds, are we not?

70
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,050
Nichiya-san!

71
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:06,950
They have never been to Edolas before!

72
00:07:06,950 --> 00:07:10,360
I bet this is the first time 
for them to see other Exceeds.

73
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:13,380
Oh, is that so?

74
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:17,620
I am the Commander of the Royal 
Guard of Extalia, Nichiya!

75
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:24,000
I'ma Nady, Extalia's Minister of State.

76
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,930
Good job completing your duty.

77
00:07:26,680 --> 00:07:27,930
Duty?

78
00:07:29,250 --> 00:07:30,890
What's the matter, Carla?

79
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:37,180
It is a bit sudden, I know, 
but the Queen awaits you.

80
00:07:37,700 --> 00:07:38,890
Follow me.

81
00:07:38,890 --> 00:07:40,520
The Queen, you say?

82
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:43,680
Carla...

83
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,170
Leave this to me.

84
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,830
I'll take a little bit and 
observe our surroundings.

85
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:52,320
I'll definitely protect you, okay?

86
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:58,560
Good work.

87
00:07:59,770 --> 00:08:01,290
More cats...

88
00:08:01,290 --> 00:08:03,410
Now then, this way!

89
00:08:04,010 --> 00:08:06,610
What in the world...

90
00:08:28,060 --> 00:08:29,600
Come, come!

91
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,690
I've got fish here, freshly caught!

92
00:08:31,690 --> 00:08:33,140
I'd like one of those, and one of those...

93
00:08:33,140 --> 00:08:35,100
Oh, and one of those, too.

94
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,200
Coming right up!

95
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:38,590
You have a lot of children, yes?

96
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:40,580
I'll throw this one in for free!

97
00:08:40,850 --> 00:08:43,280
Oh my, you're always so generous!

98
00:08:43,280 --> 00:08:49,020
Well, it's the Queen's great benevolence 
that allows me to run this shop every day.

99
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,610
Indeed...

100
00:08:50,610 --> 00:08:51,730
Thanks for coming!

101
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,860
For real!

102
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:57,540
I saw it when I went to the 
surface to gather info!

103
00:08:57,540 --> 00:08:59,540
What did you see?

104
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:02,750
A caterpillar like, this big!

105
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:04,660
You big liar!

106
00:09:04,660 --> 00:09:08,560
There's no way there could 
be a caterpillar that big!

107
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:11,600
You see, the human king...

108
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:15,090
He is controlled by we Exceeds...

109
00:09:18,820 --> 00:09:19,910
Over here, over here!

110
00:09:19,910 --> 00:09:21,360
Wait!

111
00:09:22,470 --> 00:09:24,260
It's a land of cats...

112
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:26,720
Ah, Nichiya-sama!

113
00:09:28,310 --> 00:09:30,660
Nady-sama, have a nice day!

114
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:32,210
Yes, and you, too!

115
00:09:32,470 --> 00:09:34,490
Wait, are they the rumored...

116
00:09:34,490 --> 00:09:37,280
They completed their duty on Earthland!

117
00:09:39,500 --> 00:09:41,540
Awesome! Hey, heroes!

118
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:44,080
Look at how beautiful she is!

119
00:09:44,460 --> 00:09:46,250
Everyone's a cat...

120
00:09:46,250 --> 00:09:49,480
We aren't cats. We're Exceeds.

121
00:09:49,750 --> 00:09:54,200
We are Exceeds, who stand 
over humans and guide them!

122
00:09:54,200 --> 00:09:55,650
Exceeds...

123
00:09:55,650 --> 00:10:01,730
And this is the kingdom of Exceeds, Extalia!

124
00:10:16,790 --> 00:10:17,830
Here they come!

125
00:10:17,830 --> 00:10:19,420
Finally!

126
00:10:21,800 --> 00:10:23,800
So, it has finally started...

127
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,700
Yes.

128
00:10:24,700 --> 00:10:27,790
With this, the kingdom 
will finally be secure.

129
00:10:27,790 --> 00:10:29,600
This is the south side...

130
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:34,000
The east and west sides are perfectly 
guarded as well, I presume?

131
00:10:34,230 --> 00:10:38,380
Actually, there's no place for any 
suspicious people to hide on the east or west side,

132
00:10:38,380 --> 00:10:40,350
so there's no need to guard it.

133
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:45,650
Hey! Don't you dare put that in the article!

134
00:10:45,650 --> 00:10:47,100
Of course not...

135
00:10:47,100 --> 00:10:50,950
I know well the kinds of things 
I should and shouldn't write.

136
00:10:50,950 --> 00:10:52,980
For I am a journalist!

137
00:11:03,140 --> 00:11:05,560
The plaza is only guarded 
on the north and south.

138
00:11:06,490 --> 00:11:09,270
There are less people to 
the north than the south.

139
00:11:10,110 --> 00:11:14,730
The ceremony will occur on the 
south side of the lacrima.

140
00:11:36,980 --> 00:11:38,250
I get it.

141
00:11:57,630 --> 00:12:01,120
Humans are just a horribly 
foolish and inferior species.

142
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:03,950
We have to keep careful 
control of them, or else...

143
00:12:03,950 --> 00:12:06,490
Furthermore, they have a horrible parfum...

144
00:12:09,450 --> 00:12:11,700
Parfum means smell.

145
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:16,680
The Queen controls the humans from here.

146
00:12:17,010 --> 00:12:19,840
The Queen has a wonderful parfum!

147
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:22,960
It's a real problem if they just 
increase their numbers too much.

148
00:12:22,960 --> 00:12:26,550
The humans that aren't needed are 
killed by the orders of the Queen.

149
00:12:27,830 --> 00:12:30,100
B-But, why?

150
00:12:30,100 --> 00:12:35,590
The Queen said that it was to rectify 
the vanishing magic situation.

151
00:12:35,590 --> 00:12:40,850
The Queen will control not just this world, 
but the humans in Earthland as well.

152
00:12:40,850 --> 00:12:43,090
She decides the death of humans?

153
00:12:43,330 --> 00:12:46,250
The Queen has the right.

154
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,430
Why, you ask?

155
00:12:47,700 --> 00:12:49,950
Because she is a god!

156
00:12:50,690 --> 00:12:51,870
God?

157
00:13:33,260 --> 00:13:36,180
What is our duty?

158
00:13:37,650 --> 00:13:41,920
Ever since I was born, I've had 
this duty planted inside me.

159
00:13:48,730 --> 00:13:52,050
She has been selected by the 
Queen's human control project...

160
00:13:53,180 --> 00:13:57,390
Exterminate the Dragonslayer, Wendy!

161
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,490
W-What do you mean, Carla?!

162
00:14:03,490 --> 00:14:04,580
Quiet.

163
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:07,630
What do you mean, exterminate Wendy?!

164
00:14:12,910 --> 00:14:13,780
Wha...

165
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:16,530
Then...

166
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:22,640
Our duty...

167
00:14:24,500 --> 00:14:26,130
What? It can't...

168
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:31,530
Ignorance was bliss for you...

169
00:14:32,710 --> 00:14:35,770
My duty was...

170
00:14:37,850 --> 00:14:40,350
...to exterminate Natsu?

171
00:14:45,710 --> 00:14:46,940
What?

172
00:14:47,890 --> 00:14:49,240
That can't...

173
00:15:28,310 --> 00:15:30,570
I... Natsu...

174
00:15:30,570 --> 00:15:32,650
Calm down, He-cat!

175
00:15:32,910 --> 00:15:35,680
We didn't complete our duty!

176
00:15:35,680 --> 00:15:37,730
We never had any intention to!

177
00:15:37,730 --> 00:15:40,780
So how is it that you think we have?

178
00:15:42,450 --> 00:15:44,100
Memory loss, perhaps?

179
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:45,700
There is nothing to be done about it.

180
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:49,270
"Overwriting" has unknown 
side-effects, after all.

181
00:15:49,270 --> 00:15:50,490
Answer me!

182
00:15:50,490 --> 00:15:52,790
I'lla explain.

183
00:15:53,430 --> 00:15:56,340
By the Queen's human control project,

184
00:15:56,340 --> 00:16:01,480
100 Exceeds were sent to 
Earthland 6 years ago.

185
00:16:02,150 --> 00:16:05,700
Once hatched from their egg, they 
would search for a Dragonslayer,

186
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:08,780
and carried information telling 
them to exterminate them.

187
00:16:12,110 --> 00:16:15,290
But the situation changed.

188
00:16:15,290 --> 00:16:20,900
The Anima that the humans created 
opened up another possibility.

189
00:16:23,080 --> 00:16:29,230
Instead of killing the humans in Earthland, 
we would use their magic power.

190
00:16:29,230 --> 00:16:33,720
And among their magic power, the Dragon 
Slayers would be an exceptionally large part!

191
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:37,470
That's why your duty was 
changed by emergency order.

192
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:47,810
To... "Lead the Dragon Slayers here."

193
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:09,590
What we really wanted was you...

194
00:17:10,510 --> 00:17:12,630
Your dragon magic power.

195
00:17:49,130 --> 00:17:50,890
I have to hurry.

196
00:17:50,890 --> 00:17:54,170
But there are too many people 
for me to make my move.

197
00:18:06,940 --> 00:18:09,290
Hey, what's that?

198
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:12,610
What? It's in celebration 
of the magic extraction!

199
00:18:21,030 --> 00:18:23,830
Just a little fireworks!

200
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,490
Fireworks!

201
00:18:27,490 --> 00:18:29,560
Yeah, do it!

202
00:18:29,560 --> 00:18:30,250
What's that?!

203
00:18:30,890 --> 00:18:32,570
I didn't hear about any fireworks!

204
00:18:36,060 --> 00:18:37,580
I'm counting on you.

205
00:18:37,580 --> 00:18:38,840
Get to it!

206
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,390
North?

207
00:18:45,860 --> 00:18:48,350
I'll leave the rest to you.

208
00:18:49,270 --> 00:18:52,100
Look, there was something written there!

209
00:18:52,100 --> 00:18:53,700
North of the plaza!

210
00:18:53,700 --> 00:18:57,260
Some suspicious fellow is after the lacrima!

211
00:18:57,260 --> 00:18:58,270
What?

212
00:18:58,270 --> 00:18:59,370
That's not good!

213
00:18:59,370 --> 00:19:00,990
The north is the back of the lacrima!

214
00:19:00,990 --> 00:19:02,490
Our defenses aren't solid enough there!

215
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:04,740
Leave a third here and head to the north!

216
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:06,630
Move the spectators back!

217
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:08,380
Move back, please!

218
00:19:08,380 --> 00:19:09,450
Get farther back!

219
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:15,800
Okay! Now I can really cut loose!

220
00:19:16,270 --> 00:19:18,460
Hey, what are you doing? Stand back!

221
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:27,100
That Mystogan guy seems fishy to 
me, but I'll trust him for now!

222
00:19:28,100 --> 00:19:29,770
Pillar of the Iron Dragon!

223
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:32,670
All according to plan.

224
00:19:34,530 --> 00:19:36,970
Sword of the Iron Dragon!

225
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,480
There's more where that came from!

226
00:19:57,860 --> 00:19:58,980
What?!

227
00:20:05,260 --> 00:20:10,930
It looks like the long-distance order 
overwriting wasn't properly transmitted.

228
00:20:10,930 --> 00:20:12,960
But it worked out in the end!

229
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:16,390
You did bring the Dragonslayers 
here, after all.

230
00:20:20,330 --> 00:20:23,130
We'll leave their conversion into 
magic power, in other words,

231
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:24,930
the Magicalization, to the humans.

232
00:20:24,930 --> 00:20:28,180
The humans are more skilled at that.

233
00:20:30,350 --> 00:20:32,110
N-No...

234
00:20:32,520 --> 00:20:36,540
I-I came to Edolas of my own free will...

235
00:20:36,540 --> 00:20:40,170
Nope. Just following orders.

236
00:20:40,460 --> 00:20:44,090
I took them to the tunnel to save everyone...

237
00:20:44,090 --> 00:20:46,340
You didn't notice?

238
00:20:46,340 --> 00:20:48,430
We guided you there.

239
00:20:48,780 --> 00:20:52,670
Happy, Carla... What in the world...

240
00:20:54,010 --> 00:20:59,170
I... I love Wendy...

241
00:20:59,170 --> 00:21:00,760
I said I wanted to protect her...

242
00:21:00,760 --> 00:21:03,420
That's just a kind of delusion.

243
00:21:03,420 --> 00:21:05,990
Your orders were changed from 
"exterminate" to "lead here".

244
00:21:05,990 --> 00:21:09,500
In order words, it was changed 
to "you mustn't kill".

245
00:21:09,500 --> 00:21:11,760
That's a lie!!

246
00:21:15,420 --> 00:21:19,710
Everything you've done 
was following our orders.

247
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:53,950
We are not puppets!!

248
00:22:00,150 --> 00:22:00,920
H-He...

249
00:22:03,850 --> 00:22:09,930
We're Fairy Tail wizards!!!

250
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:23,350
Happy...

251
00:23:55,520 --> 00:23:58,670
Okay! Time to go pick everyone up!

252
00:23:58,670 --> 00:23:59,600
Aye, sir!

253
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:03,130
Let me grab onto you and 
we'll fly there in a jiffy!

254
00:24:03,130 --> 00:24:05,570
Except we can't use magic!

255
00:24:05,570 --> 00:24:07,590
Hey, get it together.

256
00:24:07,590 --> 00:24:10,200
A Happy that can't fly's 
just some talking cat.

257
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:13,550
Natsu, that's a very hurtful 
thing you just said.

258
00:24:13,550 --> 00:24:16,590
Next time: Fly! To Your Friends!

259
00:24:16,590 --> 00:24:20,570
If I'm just a cat, then what's 
a Natsu who can't shoot flames?

260
00:24:20,570 --> 00:24:22,580
A Salamander who can't shoot flames...

261
00:24:22,580 --> 00:24:23,450
A Mander?

262
00:24:23,450 --> 00:24:24,690
Huh?

